WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
-= www.OpenSubtitles.org =-

04:15.603 --> 04:17.093
Get... Get...

04:27.448 --> 04:28.415
Up!

04:42.196 --> 04:43.561
You missed!

04:43.631 --> 04:48.933
You missed this time,
you little menace!

04:49.003 --> 04:51.972
I beat you!

04:53.140 --> 04:54.801
Morning.

05:08.022 --> 05:10.991
Honey, you're getting
all upset over nothing.

05:11.058 --> 05:13.151
- I'm not getting...
- Here.

05:13.227 --> 05:16.094
A nice breakfast
will cheer you up.

05:18.732 --> 05:21.064
I am not
getting upset over...

05:22.703 --> 05:26.469
- What is that?
- It's bacon.

05:27.575 --> 05:29.372
I know it's bacon.

05:29.443 --> 05:32.412
What have you done to it?

05:32.480 --> 05:35.472
You said you didn't like
all the grease from fried bacon...

05:35.549 --> 05:37.847
so I boiled it.

05:45.192 --> 05:48.320
What is Lane doing up
at this hour on a Sunday?

05:48.395 --> 05:51.626
Doesn't he turn to dust
if the sun hits him before noon?

05:51.699 --> 05:54.293
It's tryouts
for the high school ski team.

05:54.368 --> 05:56.734
He's going up
to Mt. Brody with Beth.

05:56.804 --> 05:58.669
Sure he's going up with Beth.

05:58.739 --> 06:00.798
He can't do anything
without that girl.

06:00.875 --> 06:04.436
I tell you, Jenny,
that boy is obsessed.

06:04.512 --> 06:06.742
Now, honey...

06:06.814 --> 06:08.247
obsessed?

06:20.995 --> 06:24.362
Do we not throw things away
when they're empty?

06:45.019 --> 06:48.386
What in the name
of all that's holy...

06:48.455 --> 06:50.389
Badger likes the prizes
you can get...

06:50.457 --> 06:52.891
from cutting the coupons
from the boxes.

06:52.960 --> 06:54.894
He's mailing them today.

06:54.962 --> 06:57.396
Can't you wait until the...

07:07.775 --> 07:12.769
Lane, a closet door can be closed
as well as it can be opened.

07:12.846 --> 07:15.406
Sorry, Dad.

07:15.482 --> 07:18.918
Dear, your breakfast
is getting cold.

07:18.986 --> 07:23.013
It's all right, Mom. I can't
have breakfast today. I got tryouts.

07:23.090 --> 07:25.684
Nervous stomach. Don't wanna
throw up from the chairlift again.

07:25.759 --> 07:29.718
Had to buy that guy
a new hat last time. Bye, Dad.

07:32.933 --> 07:36.596
Memorandum. I would like to
take a meeting with you tonight...

07:36.670 --> 07:40.800
to discuss that vehicle
you purchased several months ago...

07:40.874 --> 07:44.674
yet has darkened our driveway,
immobile, ever since.

07:44.745 --> 07:46.679
Okay, Dad. Noted.

07:46.747 --> 07:48.681
Talk to you tonight.
I gotta pick up Beth.

08:17.945 --> 08:19.412
Ricky.

08:26.487 --> 08:28.921
Don't be so shy. Come on.

08:33.092 --> 08:36.859
Monique, this is Ricky.

08:37.931 --> 08:40.399
Ricky, this is Monique...

08:40.467 --> 08:43.765
the French foreign exchange student
who'll be staying with us.

09:07.394 --> 09:09.692
It's an awesome spectacle...

09:09.763 --> 09:13.324
<i>and a vicious display</i>
<i>of seething opponents...</i>

09:13.400 --> 09:18.099
once again paralleled
in an obstinate attempt to prove...

09:18.172 --> 09:23.769
superiority of the roads
unequal in our lifetime.

09:23.844 --> 09:29.282
<i>The crowds swell with anticipation</i>
<i>as the lights turn green!</i>

09:39.426 --> 09:42.361
You stupid bonehead!
I'm gonna activate your dental plan!

09:42.429 --> 09:46.433
Come here, you idiot!
Get out of this car!

09:46.567 --> 09:49.263
If he asks me out,
of course I'm gonna go out with him.

09:49.336 --> 09:52.066
I mean, he skis the K-12.

09:52.139 --> 09:54.937
Yeah. He's so boss.

09:57.010 --> 10:00.776
I'll tell him after tryouts. You
know how he gets when he gets upset.

10:00.847 --> 10:03.782
Yeah. From the chairlift.

10:03.850 --> 10:07.217
He had to buy the guy
a new hat last time.

10:07.955 --> 10:11.447
Lane's here. I gotta go.
I'll call you later. Bye.

10:45.058 --> 10:47.026
He's the only person
in Greendale...

10:47.094 --> 10:51.258
that's ever skied the K-12
from the glacier and lived.

11:13.820 --> 11:16.311
Man, what a hunk.

11:28.435 --> 11:31.268
Listen up.
Your running time has to be...

11:31.338 --> 11:34.136
under 58 seconds to even
be considered for the team.

11:34.207 --> 11:36.903
Your time will be gauged
along with a rating...

11:36.977 --> 11:41.471
of one to ten on your style,
which will be judged solely by me...

11:41.548 --> 11:44.142
and my vast expertise
of skiing technique.

11:44.217 --> 11:48.847
Why don't we have you sorry-looking
lot of hopefuls make your way up.

11:48.922 --> 11:52.414
You future members of the girls'
ski team can all keep me company...

11:52.492 --> 11:54.722
until it's time
for you to take the track.

11:54.795 --> 11:57.889
- Who'd like to hold my clipboard?
- Me! Me!

12:00.500 --> 12:02.434
You'll make a fine little helper.
What's your name?

12:02.502 --> 12:06.233
- Charles De Mar.
- Shut up, geek.

12:08.308 --> 12:10.833
- What's your name?
- Beth.

12:10.911 --> 12:12.776
That's my favorite name.

12:15.615 --> 12:19.051
- <i>Buenos días.</i> Roy Stalin.
- <i>Hola.</i> Lane Myer.

12:19.119 --> 12:21.952
I can see you and I
share one common desire...

12:23.190 --> 12:26.057
the desire to be a part
of the well-oiled machinery...

12:26.126 --> 12:29.061
that is the Greendale
High School ski-racing team.

12:29.129 --> 12:31.791
- The desire for victory.
- Well, I...

12:31.865 --> 12:34.026
Right on! Get up there,
and let's see what you got.

12:43.210 --> 12:46.543
- Ready up there?
- <i>Yeah. We're all set.</i>

12:46.613 --> 12:48.604
What is the next victim's name?

12:48.682 --> 12:51.082
"Myer. Lane Myer."

12:51.151 --> 12:53.881
Is that as in Oscar Mayer?

12:53.954 --> 12:55.751
That's a roger, dude.

12:55.822 --> 12:58.518
You were standing with Oscar.

12:58.592 --> 13:02.050
Is he your main wiener man?

13:02.129 --> 13:05.792
Don't listen to Stalin, kid.
He's a punk.

13:05.866 --> 13:07.800
Now, you show 'em, Rock.

13:07.868 --> 13:10.666
You show 'em how a skier
really skis.

13:10.737 --> 13:14.332
- We're sending him down.
- That's a roger. Counting down.

13:15.242 --> 13:17.301
<i>Drei,</i> fry. Go!

13:44.371 --> 13:48.637
Too bad. Real close. Next.

13:48.708 --> 13:52.041
<i>Listen. I think we should talk.</i>

13:52.112 --> 13:54.080
<i>We've been seeing an awful lot</i>
<i>of each other lately...</i>

13:54.147 --> 13:55.910
<i>and I really think</i>
<i>it's in my best interest...</i>

13:55.982 --> 13:58.576
<i>if I went out</i>
<i>with someone more popular...</i>

13:58.652 --> 14:01.348
<i>better looking,</i>
<i>drives a nicer car.</i>

14:05.325 --> 14:10.092
Six months! Six months,
and she dumps me for him.

14:10.163 --> 14:12.495
For Stalin. Just like that.

14:12.566 --> 14:14.500
Six damn months!

14:20.173 --> 14:25.008
Truly a sight to behold...
a man beaten.

14:25.078 --> 14:27.069
<i>The once-great champ...</i>

14:27.147 --> 14:30.878
now a study in mawkishness.

14:30.951 --> 14:33.852
<i>No longer</i>
<i>the victory-hungry stallion...</i>

14:33.920 --> 14:37.185
- All right.
<i>- We've raced so many times before...</i>

14:37.257 --> 14:39.248
but a pathetic...

14:39.326 --> 14:42.022
washed-up, aged ex-champion.

14:42.095 --> 14:43.528
Let's go!

14:50.003 --> 14:52.403
Someone's gonna see God.

14:55.141 --> 14:57.302
I'm gonna break
your goddamn neck!

14:57.377 --> 15:00.039
Get outta the car!

15:00.113 --> 15:02.206
Get outta the car!

15:06.653 --> 15:08.917
Hello. How was your day?

15:08.989 --> 15:12.789
- Beth broke up with me.
- That's nice.

15:12.859 --> 15:14.793
We're through. That's it.

15:29.175 --> 15:31.643
What the hell?
Wait a minute here.

15:32.779 --> 15:34.713
Wait. This is death here.

15:36.983 --> 15:39.349
I haven't even been
to New York City.

15:39.419 --> 15:41.910
Jesus. I haven't
even been anywhere.

15:52.465 --> 15:56.026
Suicide is never the answer,
little trooper.

15:56.102 --> 15:59.765
Greendale is a bodaciously
small town.

15:59.839 --> 16:02.171
It's a flyspeck on the map...

16:02.242 --> 16:04.369
a rest stop on the way
to a ski slope.

16:04.444 --> 16:06.912
I can't even get real drugs
here.

16:08.048 --> 16:12.246
Stalin's a hero, the only one
in this town who can ski the K-12.

16:12.319 --> 16:15.482
You're a great skier,
but he's incredible.

16:16.856 --> 16:19.825
What if I ski the K-12?
You think she'd take me back?

16:22.829 --> 16:25.263
I'm back to suicide again.

16:30.370 --> 16:33.673
<i>I think we're all going</i>
<i>to enjoy this little treat.</i>

16:33.807 --> 16:36.571
I got the recipe
from the <i>Ladies'HomeJournal.</i>

16:36.643 --> 16:40.010
The mail got wet in the rain,
so some of the pages ran together.

16:40.079 --> 16:44.038
But what I couldn't read
I improvised with my own ideas.

16:44.117 --> 16:47.780
You see, it's got raisins in it.

16:48.855 --> 16:50.789
You like raisins.

16:52.592 --> 16:56.858
There is still one more thing
I would like to discuss with Lane.

16:58.164 --> 17:00.189
The subject is...

17:02.702 --> 17:05.671
is the mystery car.

17:07.140 --> 17:09.540
Thank you, honey.

17:09.608 --> 17:12.839
Which even as we speak...

17:12.912 --> 17:15.574
darkens our domain
under a moldy tarp.

17:15.647 --> 17:18.208
You do know the car
of which I speak?

17:18.284 --> 17:20.752
- Yeah. I just never...
- Let me refresh your memory.

17:20.819 --> 17:23.084
Cast your mind back.

17:23.156 --> 17:25.589
It's a crisp September morning.

17:25.657 --> 17:29.856
You borrowed $200 from me
to purchase the car...

17:29.929 --> 17:33.126
mainly because
your girlfriend Beth said it was...

17:33.199 --> 17:35.565
I believe the term was "tasty."

17:35.635 --> 17:38.570
Since then, that "tasty" car...

17:38.638 --> 17:42.904
has slept in an auto cocoon
on my front lawn.

17:44.277 --> 17:46.711
I'll get around to it.

17:48.181 --> 17:51.878
Have you seen the exchange student
who's staying at the Smiths's house?

17:51.951 --> 17:54.044
Perhaps you should go over
and welcome her to our town.

17:54.120 --> 17:56.054
I think she would like that.

17:56.122 --> 17:58.386
Mrs. Smith probably got her
so that weirdo son...

17:58.458 --> 18:01.393
could see what
a real girl looks like.

18:01.461 --> 18:04.521
You know,
he never goes outdoors.

18:04.597 --> 18:07.259
Just sits in that house,
crochets all day long.

18:07.333 --> 18:09.267
The Chapmans had
their exchange student...

18:09.335 --> 18:11.269
stay with them for six months.

18:11.337 --> 18:13.737
He practically became a son
to Jules and Irene.

18:13.806 --> 18:15.706
You mean that kid
from El Salvador?

18:15.775 --> 18:18.369
Can I be excused?
I'm not feeling well.

18:19.445 --> 18:21.379
I'm just gonna be excused.

18:33.693 --> 18:36.321
I can't figure it out, Badger.

18:36.396 --> 18:40.992
You seem smart. Why waste your time
with all this kid-stuff garbage?

18:44.370 --> 18:46.304
You're almost eight.

19:05.558 --> 19:07.992
It was love at first sight.

19:12.832 --> 19:14.766
<i>Red dog! Red dog!</i>

19:14.834 --> 19:17.894
92, 74, 16, 43!

19:17.971 --> 19:19.905
Bring it home, mama!

19:28.181 --> 19:30.115
Got it! Got it!

19:56.676 --> 19:58.610
So, how do you
like Greendale?

19:59.679 --> 20:01.112
Fine.

20:03.716 --> 20:06.913
And the school system,
you find it adequate?

20:06.986 --> 20:10.387
School hasn't started yet.

20:10.456 --> 20:13.118
<i>She itched her nose.</i>
<i>I wonder if that was...</i>

20:13.192 --> 20:16.161
<i>some kind of message to me</i>
<i>that there's something on my nose.</i>

20:16.229 --> 20:19.960
<i>That's funny.</i>
<i>He wiped his nose after I did.</i>

20:20.033 --> 20:23.196
<i>Maybe I got dirt on my nose</i>
<i>when I itched it.</i>

20:23.269 --> 20:25.897
<i>God, he's too embarrassed</i>
<i>to tell me.</i>

20:25.972 --> 20:28.566
<i>I must look sickening.</i>

20:28.641 --> 20:30.575
<i>There she goes again.</i>
<i>What could it be?</i>

20:30.643 --> 20:32.634
<i>Dirt? Relish?</i>

20:32.712 --> 20:34.646
<i>Relish on my nose? How gross.</i>

20:34.714 --> 20:36.648
- <i>She might think it's...</i>
- Usually Nazis.

20:36.716 --> 20:39.344
<i>Not that. Please don't</i>
<i>let it be a booger.</i>

20:39.419 --> 20:42.081
<i>Not now. Please, God.</i>

21:05.445 --> 21:08.039
I don't get it. How could...

21:08.114 --> 21:11.174
How could she
throw away six months?

21:11.250 --> 21:14.378
I mean, six months?

21:14.454 --> 21:17.014
Just like that?

21:17.090 --> 21:19.650
No explanation, no reason.

21:19.726 --> 21:22.593
Just throw it away.

21:22.662 --> 21:24.596
Doesn't...

21:24.664 --> 21:26.598
How can you just
throw away six months?

21:26.666 --> 21:29.601
I mean, when you're
in love with someone...

21:30.803 --> 21:33.465
Six months is just...
I'm history.

21:33.539 --> 21:35.973
Just bam!
Like that, I'm gone.

21:37.176 --> 21:39.440
She's probably just testing me.

21:39.512 --> 21:41.446
A big test.

21:41.514 --> 21:45.280
That's probably... That's her.

21:45.351 --> 21:47.785
That's her.

21:52.358 --> 21:55.555
- Johnny.
- Four weeks.

21:55.628 --> 21:58.461
Twenty papers.
That's two dollars.

21:58.531 --> 22:02.160
- Plus tip.
- I don't have a dime. Sorry.

22:03.069 --> 22:05.594
Didn't ask for a dime.

22:05.671 --> 22:08.003
Two dollars.

22:08.074 --> 22:11.475
Well, it's funny, see.
My mom had to leave early...

22:11.544 --> 22:13.808
to take my brother to school
and my dad to work 'cause...

22:13.880 --> 22:17.646
Two dollars. Cash.

22:17.717 --> 22:20.880
The problem here is...
my little brother, this morning...

22:20.953 --> 22:23.513
got his arm caught
in the microwave and...

22:23.589 --> 22:26.319
and my grandmother dropped acid
and freaked out...

22:26.392 --> 22:29.122
and hijacked a school bus
full of penguins.

22:29.195 --> 22:31.129
So it's kind of a family crisis.

22:31.197 --> 22:33.131
So come back later? Great.

22:41.274 --> 22:44.732
<i>Breakin'up is hard to do</i>

22:44.811 --> 22:47.439
<i>Don't take your love...</i>

22:47.513 --> 22:51.813
<i>- To me, and she's gone</i>
<i>- And she's gone</i>

22:51.884 --> 22:55.012
<i>Fifty ways to leave your lover</i>

22:55.087 --> 22:57.248
<i>Hurts so bad</i>

22:57.323 --> 23:02.693
<i>They say that breakin'up</i>
<i>is hard to do...</i>

23:05.498 --> 23:10.834
<i>The three cardinal</i>
<i>trapezoidal formations...</i>

23:10.903 --> 23:14.031
hereto made orientable
in our diagram...

23:14.106 --> 23:16.040
by connecting
the various points...

23:16.108 --> 23:20.340
HIGK, PEGQ and LMNO...

23:20.413 --> 23:24.611
creating our geometric
configurations...

23:24.684 --> 23:29.121
which have no properties,
but with location...

23:30.523 --> 23:36.120
are equal to
the described triangle CAB...

23:36.195 --> 23:37.628
quintuplicated.

23:38.698 --> 23:40.131
Therefore...

23:42.101 --> 23:44.194
it is also
the five triangles...

23:44.270 --> 23:47.000
composing
the aforementioned NIGH.

23:47.073 --> 23:52.143
Each are equal to the triangle
CAB in this geometric concept.

23:52.277 --> 23:55.678
Therefore, in a like manner...

23:55.747 --> 23:58.045
the geometric metaphors...

23:58.116 --> 24:01.176
can derive
a repeated vectoral sum.

24:02.253 --> 24:04.653
This was your assignment...

24:05.423 --> 24:08.324
and I would like
to see the results.

24:08.393 --> 24:11.453
Please, take them out.

24:34.886 --> 24:37.116
Oops.

24:37.188 --> 24:38.621
Sophia.

24:39.991 --> 24:43.620
- And Buster.
- Please!

24:43.695 --> 24:47.290
- Me! Me!
- And... Beth.

24:49.367 --> 24:51.665
- And...
- Please! Please!

24:51.736 --> 24:56.298
- Please, please!
- Mr. Myer.

24:56.374 --> 24:58.308
Please join us
at the blackboard...

24:58.376 --> 25:02.779
and show us your solution
to this paltry geometric dilemma.

25:25.803 --> 25:27.236
Sorry.

25:59.537 --> 26:01.732
For God's sakes,
would you relax?

26:01.806 --> 26:04.934
- It's just our virginity.
- Yeah, I agree totally.

26:05.009 --> 26:07.170
I feel like we should tell someone
or do something.

26:07.245 --> 26:09.736
I can get my dad's Polaroid
or something.

26:11.249 --> 26:13.274
- What was that?
- What was what?

26:13.351 --> 26:15.285
I heard something.

26:15.353 --> 26:17.913
We're in the most secluded place
in the Northern Hemisphere.

26:17.989 --> 26:20.423
I assure you
we are totally alone.

26:23.327 --> 26:24.760
Come on.

26:28.366 --> 26:30.231
What's wrong?

26:30.301 --> 26:32.895
That thing I put on me...
it broke.

26:34.272 --> 26:36.604
Broke? It broke?

26:36.674 --> 26:39.472
- Take it easy. I'll buy a new one.
- I don't want a new one!

26:39.544 --> 26:42.741
- Do you know what that means?
- I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

26:52.957 --> 26:56.757
Now, now.
I'll see you all tomorrow.

26:56.828 --> 27:01.891
Just remember to memorize pages
39 to 110 for tomorrow's lesson.

27:01.966 --> 27:04.093
- All right!
- Cool!

27:10.641 --> 27:12.575
I just can't wait
till tomorrow.

27:13.811 --> 27:15.745
Wait for me at my locker.

27:17.682 --> 27:19.115
Listen...

27:19.183 --> 27:21.583
I've been thinking about what
you told me last night...

27:21.652 --> 27:23.745
and I've decided
I'm gonna help you.

27:23.821 --> 27:25.254
How?

27:26.958 --> 27:30.951
I've been going to this high school
for 71/2 years.

27:32.029 --> 27:33.792
I'm no dummy.

27:33.865 --> 27:36.095
I know high school girls.

27:37.168 --> 27:39.762
Two things. One...

27:39.837 --> 27:42.271
how about your sax?

27:42.340 --> 27:45.468
The thing about Roy is
he plays the guitar.

27:45.543 --> 27:48.103
- He does?
- Yeah. Girls love that.

27:48.179 --> 27:52.172
- Why don't you take up sax again?
- Number two?

27:53.784 --> 27:56.309
The K-12, dude.

27:56.387 --> 27:58.617
You make a gnarly run
like that...

27:58.689 --> 28:02.056
and girls will get sterile
just looking at you.

28:04.962 --> 28:08.056
Would you stay behind?
I'd like a word with you.

28:10.134 --> 28:11.897
We'll do this.

28:11.969 --> 28:13.664
Talk to you later.

28:16.541 --> 28:17.974
Yes, sir?

28:20.044 --> 28:22.478
This is a bit awkward.

28:22.547 --> 28:23.980
Yes, sir.

28:25.483 --> 28:26.916
Well...

28:28.219 --> 28:30.414
I've heard a few things, and...

28:32.490 --> 28:35.482
Well, I was wondering...

28:35.560 --> 28:37.585
if you would mind
if I took out Beth.

29:32.183 --> 29:34.151
<i>And I love you so much</i>

29:37.555 --> 29:41.992
<i>'Cause I met you</i>
<i>in first grade</i>

29:42.059 --> 29:43.890
<i>Yes, I love you</i>

29:55.973 --> 29:57.998
What'd you go
and do that for?

30:00.911 --> 30:02.845
Really. Why?

30:02.913 --> 30:04.175
That's sick.

30:04.248 --> 30:08.617
"Sick"? I love you.
How could you dump me for him?

30:08.686 --> 30:12.122
Face it.
You're a no-show, a loss.

30:12.189 --> 30:15.522
You're immature. You can't do
